  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2012-02-28",
    "date": "2012-04-02T18:45:09Z",
    "text": "Presidential Allowance Modernization Act - Revises provisions relating to presidential pensions to\u00a0allow former\u00a0Presidents\u00a0an annuity\u00a0of $200,000\u00a0and an additional monetary\u00a0allowance\u00a0of $200,000 per year. Reduces such pension by the amount that a President's adjusted gross income in a taxable year exceeds $400,000.\u00a0\n\nIncreases from $20,000 to $100,000 the annual annuity of a surviving spouse of a former President."
  },
